\begin_layout Plain Layout
color depth
\end_layout

\end_inset

Color depth 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The display color depth must be set to 24-bit or 32-bit.
 Most Table Maps are designed for 32-bit color depth, so your display should
 be set to that for maximum compatibility with others’ work.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Display 
\begin_inset Index
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
resolution
\end_layout

\end_inset

resolution 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You need enough display resolution to contain both the poker client window
 and OpenHoldem at it smallest size (i.e.
 table view off).
 In general, the minimum acceptable display resolution is 1024x768.
 The smaller resolutions 800x600 and 640x480 do not have enough real estate
 to show both the poker client and OpenHoldem without overlapping windows.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
